South Africans have been warned that if they do not comply with the Level-4 nationwide lockdown regulations the country could revert back to Level-5 restrictions. This was said by Co-operative Governance Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced that the lockdown regulations will be lowered from Level-5 to Level-4 on May 1. Dlamini-Zuma says the rate of coronavirus infection will determine which level the country will move to. According to SA’s risk-adjustment strategy for economic activity, Level-4 is expected to be “moderate to high virus spread, with moderate readiness”. However, some leisure and social activities will remain prohibited through all lockdown levels. Below are the 10 things that must be known about level 4 lockdown. 